From 65ba179e36765f79c659592c6428dbecae9515c7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 11 Jul 2026 06:41:23 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix admin logout, remove admin add-food capability, and fix
 vendorId column mismatch
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- Admin dashboard (UserData.tsx) had no logout affordance at all (unlike the
  vendor and user areas, which both already had one). Added a logout button
  that clears auth state and redirects to /login. The empty AdminLogin.tsx
  and unused admin AddFood.tsx were dead files (App.tsx logs admin in via the
  existing Login.tsx role picker against /api/admin/login) — removed both.

- Per the intended design (admin approves vendors + moderates food; vendors
  own their menu via VendorMenu.tsx), removed the admin "Add Menu Item" route
  (/admin/addFood) and nav link, and restricted POST/PUT /api/food to the
  vendor role only in FoodRoutes.js. Added an admin-only PATCH
  /api/food/:id/flag endpoint (FoodController.flagFood) backed by a new
  isFlagged column on FoodModel, and a "Food Items" tab in the admin
  dashboard to flag/unflag and delete (DELETE /api/food/:id, already
  admin+vendor) any item — replacing admin's create capability with
  moderation as intended.

- Root-caused the "Unknown column 'vendorId' in field list" error on
  /vendor/setup and the restaurants not appearing on the site: both are the
  same bug. Server.js called db.sync() (no options), which only creates
  tables that don't exist yet — it never adds new columns to a table that's
  already deployed. vendorId was added to RestrauntModel after the
  restaurants table already existed on Railway, so every INSERT/SELECT
  referencing it (restaurant creation, and the vendorId-based approval
  filtering in getAllRestaurants) failed against the live schema. Switched
  both Server.js and seed.js to db.sync({ alter: true }) so Sequelize
  reconciles column differences on boot instead of silently no-op'ing.
